HEADWORD: ozone paper
<hw>o"zone pa"per</hw>. <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Paper coated with starch
and potassium iodine, also called <altname>starch-iodide
paper</altname>. It turns blue when exposed to ozone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

